WEBVTT

00:00:49.274 --> 00:00:51.335
Beautiful love stories

00:00:51.335 --> 00:00:53.554
always begin

00:00:53.554 --> 00:00:56.480
with a fateful first meeting.

00:00:59.242 --> 00:01:01.953
But these days,
men and women don't just sit back

00:01:01.953 --> 00:01:05.812
and wait for destiny to find them.

00:01:05.812 --> 00:01:06.836
[When you need a fresh start]

00:01:06.836 --> 00:01:08.981
[A Rebound Relationship]

00:01:08.981 --> 00:01:11.460
They choose who they're drawn to.

00:01:11.460 --> 00:01:12.951
They decide

00:01:12.951 --> 00:01:15.784
when to begin and when to end it.

00:01:19.271 --> 00:01:20.362
This is an era

00:01:20.362 --> 00:01:22.938
where everyone takes control of
their own love life.

00:01:22.938 --> 00:01:23.983
And me?

00:01:23.983 --> 00:01:26.602
I'm looking for love too.

00:01:34.728 --> 00:01:37.280
Excuse me, are you here for the blind date?

00:01:37.280 --> 00:01:39.241
Yes, that's right.

00:01:41.641 --> 00:01:44.708
Hi. I'm Song Tae Seop.

00:01:44.708 --> 00:01:47.347
I'm Lee Ui Yeong.

00:01:48.894 --> 00:01:50.681
7:00 p.m. sharp.

00:01:50.681 --> 00:01:52.421
Right in the middle of
the busiest part of town,

00:01:52.421 --> 00:01:54.042
I meet this person.

00:01:54.042 --> 00:01:56.335
Could this be

00:01:56.335 --> 00:01:58.221
the start of the love of my life?

00:01:58.221 --> 00:02:00.560
[Episode 1]

00:02:02.025 --> 00:02:05.251
[One Month Earlier]

00:02:13.943 --> 00:02:16.337
Why even set an alarm

00:02:16.337 --> 00:02:19.432
if you are not going to get up?

00:02:19.432 --> 00:02:21.002
Come on, wake up.

00:02:21.002 --> 00:02:22.286
That hurts.

00:02:22.286 --> 00:02:25.742
Did you lay all this out
so you could just walk all over it?

00:02:25.742 --> 00:02:28.504
If you are done with that face mask,
throw it away.

00:02:28.504 --> 00:02:29.543
Seriously.

00:02:29.543 --> 00:02:31.286
Mom.

00:02:31.286 --> 00:02:32.836
I was going to sleep a little longer.

00:02:32.836 --> 00:02:34.921
You are so loud.

00:02:39.718 --> 00:02:40.743
Yes.

00:02:40.743 --> 00:02:42.876
[Hanbit Health Insurance for Women]
Of course.

00:02:42.876 --> 00:02:45.433
But I would not recommend canceling.

00:02:45.433 --> 00:02:47.017
With your medical history,

00:02:47.017 --> 00:02:50.645
you might not be able to re-enroll later.

00:02:50.645 --> 00:02:54.036
Usually, at your age,

00:02:54.036 --> 00:02:56.974
we start seeing more surgical cases.

00:02:56.974 --> 00:02:59.196
Right.

00:02:59.196 --> 00:03:01.435
[Chore Chart]
With the economy like this,

00:03:01.435 --> 00:03:03.712
many clients call
trying to reduce their premiums.

00:03:03.712 --> 00:03:05.263
You're working hard even on the weekend.

00:03:05.263 --> 00:03:07.656
If you think about it,
it is the cost of one weekend brunch.

00:03:07.656 --> 00:03:09.795
Would it not be wiser
to cut unnecessary spending

00:03:09.795 --> 00:03:12.302
and invest in your health?

00:03:12.302 --> 00:03:13.594
- Yes.
- You're good at this.

00:03:13.594 --> 00:03:14.660
What about wedding gift money?

00:03:14.660 --> 00:03:16.658
That line is very current.

00:03:16.658 --> 00:03:18.251
Prices are up, and at your age,

00:03:18.251 --> 00:03:21.293
you probably have quite a few monthly expenses.

00:03:21.293 --> 00:03:22.810
If you're not planning to get married,

00:03:22.810 --> 00:03:25.393
maybe it's time to stop
the gift-exchange cycle.

00:03:25.393 --> 00:03:28.683
I don't even attend weddings anymore.

00:03:28.683 --> 00:03:31.390
I doubt I'd ever get that money back.

00:03:31.390 --> 00:03:33.813
That's exactly the kind of coverage

00:03:33.813 --> 00:03:36.633
no one can actually afford.

00:03:36.633 --> 00:03:38.343
What?

00:03:38.343 --> 00:03:40.220
Wait, seriously?

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:41.550
Even if you skip the ceremony,

00:03:41.550 --> 00:03:43.550
you still send wedding money every time, right?

00:03:43.550 --> 00:03:44.833
- No.
- "No?"

00:03:44.833 --> 00:03:47.285
I take pride in my work.

00:03:47.285 --> 00:03:50.420
I don't lie to clients
just to sell more insurance.

00:03:50.420 --> 00:03:51.456
Hey.

00:03:51.456 --> 00:03:53.642
But is that really something
to be this upset about?

00:03:53.642 --> 00:03:55.329
Yeah. It hurts.

00:03:55.329 --> 00:03:58.055
Isn't raising your kid
and waiting for the harvest

00:03:58.055 --> 00:03:59.381
what moms look forward to?

00:03:59.381 --> 00:04:02.647
How am I supposed to wait
for something that is never going to happen?

00:04:02.647 --> 00:04:03.677
That's just a waste.

00:04:03.677 --> 00:04:08.457
You never date, so I thought maybe you were
anti-marriage, anti-relationship.

00:04:08.457 --> 00:04:12.020
No. I'm not anti-marriage or anti-relationship.

00:04:12.020 --> 00:04:14.098
I just...

00:04:14.098 --> 00:04:17.244
So you just can't get a boyfriend?

00:04:17.244 --> 00:04:19.377
Four years.

00:04:19.377 --> 00:04:20.949
The guy you dated

00:04:20.949 --> 00:04:24.088
while I was studying for my certification
was your ex.

00:04:24.088 --> 00:04:25.166
Don't you remember?

00:04:25.166 --> 00:04:26.908
After that breakup,
you were crying while working out.

00:04:26.908 --> 00:04:31.622
You were dropping dumbbells
because they were soaked in tears.

00:04:33.356 --> 00:04:35.208
It feels like four months.

00:04:35.208 --> 00:04:37.573
How is that four years ago?

00:04:37.573 --> 00:04:40.980
They say as you get older
and your body starts to age,

00:04:40.980 --> 00:04:43.338
you move through life more slowly,

00:04:43.338 --> 00:04:46.867
so time feels like it goes by faster.

00:04:46.867 --> 00:04:48.884
Okay. Which means...

00:04:48.884 --> 00:04:51.641
we should hurry to the next set.

00:04:51.641 --> 00:04:53.401
Hey, by the way...

00:04:53.401 --> 00:04:57.005
Instead of "aging,"
could you say "maturing and growing?"

00:04:57.005 --> 00:04:58.892
No.

00:04:58.892 --> 00:05:01.165
Here.

00:05:01.165 --> 00:05:03.367
Lower it and hold for four seconds.

00:05:03.367 --> 00:05:05.525
One!

00:05:05.525 --> 00:05:06.989
See? You've grown.

00:05:06.989 --> 00:05:10.798
You used to struggle with one kilo,
now you're lifting four, huh?

00:05:10.798 --> 00:05:12.045
Two!

00:05:12.045 --> 00:05:14.049
Still, your juniors respect you at work.

00:05:14.049 --> 00:05:15.957
And your seniors see you as competition.

00:05:15.957 --> 00:05:17.156
Right?

00:05:17.156 --> 00:05:19.602
Hey, I'm getting a call.

00:05:23.988 --> 00:05:25.484
- Hello?
- Ms. Ui Yeong!

00:05:25.484 --> 00:05:26.694
What on earth did you do?

00:05:26.694 --> 00:05:28.917
Get to the hotel now!

00:05:31.181 --> 00:05:33.204
I just got a call
from the restaurant's sous-chef.

00:05:33.204 --> 00:05:34.667
We're way short on cod.

00:05:34.667 --> 00:05:37.141
You know the U.K. Embassy banquet tonight.

00:05:37.141 --> 00:05:39.417
Yes, the guests' preferences were taken into...

00:05:39.417 --> 00:05:41.098
- Sorry.
- Oh, watch out!

00:05:41.098 --> 00:05:42.243
We finalized the menu...

00:05:42.243 --> 00:05:43.794
and projected demand based on that.

00:05:43.794 --> 00:05:45.594
We already purchased
the ingredients accordingly.

00:05:45.594 --> 00:05:47.130
- Hello.
- You didn't factor in the embassy's request.

00:05:48.031 --> 00:05:50.216
- The U.K. side asked to add fish and chips...
- Hello.

00:05:50.216 --> 00:05:51.386
since there wasn't a British menu item.

00:05:52.577 --> 00:05:54.208
Is this really the time to be shocked?

00:05:54.208 --> 00:05:56.331
Eighty cod. I need them by two.
Fresh, not frozen.

00:05:56.331 --> 00:05:58.060
Two? Eighty?

00:05:58.060 --> 00:06:00.324
Where are we even supposed to find
that much cod right now...

00:06:00.324 --> 00:06:01.336
"Where?"

00:06:01.336 --> 00:06:04.205
Why are you asking me?

00:06:04.205 --> 00:06:06.446
Oh, General Manager.

00:06:06.446 --> 00:06:10.245
Yeah, my team still has a lot to learn.

00:06:10.245 --> 00:06:11.442
Don't worry.

00:06:11.442 --> 00:06:14.284
We'll have everything ready on time.

00:06:14.284 --> 00:06:17.303
- I know how hard everyone's working.
- Thank you.

00:06:20.612 --> 00:06:22.229
- Hello.
- Thank you for your effort.

00:06:22.229 --> 00:06:24.078
Thank you.

00:06:24.078 --> 00:06:26.609
All right, everyone. Keep it up.

00:06:33.688 --> 00:06:35.036
[2nd Floor: Dried Seafood Market]

00:06:35.036 --> 00:06:38.030
But adding a dish on the day of the event?
Isn't that a bit much?

00:06:38.030 --> 00:06:39.648
The embassy secretary apparently promised

00:06:39.648 --> 00:06:42.276
they'd host their next event at our hotel,
so they pushed for it.

00:06:42.276 --> 00:06:44.704
Well, then we have to do it.

00:06:44.704 --> 00:06:46.834
But can we even find eighty cod around here?

00:06:46.834 --> 00:06:48.234
We have to. Somehow.

00:06:48.234 --> 00:06:50.707
This is insane.

00:06:55.215 --> 00:06:57.199
I thought you just dressed sloppy at work

00:06:57.199 --> 00:06:58.686
because you didn't care,

00:06:58.686 --> 00:07:00.811
but turns out this is you trying your hardest.

00:07:00.811 --> 00:07:02.096
Cute.

00:07:02.096 --> 00:07:04.589
Come on, I came straight from the gym.

00:07:04.589 --> 00:07:06.566
Anyway, how much cod have we secured?

00:07:06.566 --> 00:07:08.666
Ten from the market,

00:07:08.666 --> 00:07:10.488
twenty coming by courier.

00:07:10.488 --> 00:07:12.013
We're still fifty short.

00:07:12.013 --> 00:07:13.700
- Hey, come on in.
- Hey.

00:07:13.700 --> 00:07:17.323
I heard you two are buying up
every last cod in town.

00:07:17.323 --> 00:07:19.560
But this is all I've got left.

00:07:19.560 --> 00:07:20.999
Seriously? We'll take all of it.

00:07:20.999 --> 00:07:22.897
But why is there so little?

00:07:22.897 --> 00:07:24.790
This was our last stop.

00:07:24.790 --> 00:07:26.004
Isn't there anywhere else?

00:07:26.004 --> 00:07:27.802
It all sold out earlier.

00:07:27.802 --> 00:07:29.793
I'll pack these up.

00:07:31.092 --> 00:07:32.600
- Hey.
- Yeah?

00:07:32.600 --> 00:07:36.523
There's a shipment headed
to Season Plaza Hotel, right?

00:07:36.523 --> 00:07:38.516
Come on, there's business etiquette.

00:07:38.516 --> 00:07:41.443
I can't just give you fish
that someone else already bought.

00:07:41.443 --> 00:07:42.917
No way.

00:07:42.917 --> 00:07:44.063
Hyun Min.

00:07:44.063 --> 00:07:45.642
- Yes?
- Take these...

00:07:45.642 --> 00:07:46.775
and head back to the hotel.

00:07:46.775 --> 00:07:47.817
What about you?

00:07:47.817 --> 00:07:49.524
We know where the cod is.

00:07:49.524 --> 00:07:50.721
I'm going.

00:07:50.721 --> 00:07:52.637
To reel it in.

00:08:06.563 --> 00:08:08.820
Hello. Would you like to check in?

00:08:08.820 --> 00:08:10.398
I'm not checking in.

00:08:10.398 --> 00:08:11.999
I actually need a favor.

00:08:13.203 --> 00:08:14.586
How can I help you?

00:08:14.586 --> 00:08:17.083
I need a phone number.

00:08:17.083 --> 00:08:19.216
This is...

00:08:19.216 --> 00:08:21.033
who I am.

00:08:21.033 --> 00:08:23.150
[Lee Ui Yeong, Purchasing Team]
I see.

00:08:23.150 --> 00:08:26.983
I really need the number of
Purchasing Team Manager in this hotel.

00:08:33.197 --> 00:08:34.720
They look great,

00:08:34.720 --> 00:08:36.074
but we don't have enough yet.

00:08:36.074 --> 00:08:37.507
Chef,

00:08:37.507 --> 00:08:39.097
with all due respect,

00:08:39.097 --> 00:08:41.162
could we maybe make it
0.8 of a portion per plate?

00:08:41.162 --> 00:08:44.082
If we puff up the batter nice and thick...

00:08:44.082 --> 00:08:46.397
That's nonsense.

00:08:46.397 --> 00:08:47.418
Chef,

00:08:47.418 --> 00:08:49.838
what about bulking it up with salad or garnish?

00:08:49.838 --> 00:08:51.172
That's basically the same thing.

00:08:51.172 --> 00:08:53.133
Exactly.

00:08:58.713 --> 00:09:00.879
Season Plaza?

00:09:00.879 --> 00:09:03.079
Thank you.

00:09:05.024 --> 00:09:06.521
Ui Yeong?

00:09:06.521 --> 00:09:09.274
Why did you come in this car?

00:09:12.373 --> 00:09:15.026
[30 Minutes Earlier]

00:09:22.237 --> 00:09:23.872
[Manager Cho Aram, Purchasing Team]

00:09:23.872 --> 00:09:25.783
I've been meaning to meet you.

00:09:25.783 --> 00:09:27.098
You know me, right?

00:09:27.098 --> 00:09:29.251
Lee Ui Yeong from Purchasing Team, The Hills.

00:09:29.251 --> 00:09:30.753
Yes, I know.

00:09:30.753 --> 00:09:31.782
What do you need?

00:09:31.782 --> 00:09:34.239
The cod that came into your hotel today.

00:09:34.239 --> 00:09:36.653
Transfer all of it to me.

00:09:36.653 --> 00:09:38.230
Why would I do that?

00:09:38.230 --> 00:09:40.456
You know...

00:09:41.757 --> 00:09:43.057
Because we're in a bind.

00:09:43.057 --> 00:09:46.666
That's why I'm here,
asking you to open up your pantry.

00:09:46.666 --> 00:09:48.010
Ms. Lee Ui Yeong,

00:09:48.010 --> 00:09:50.793
you're even bolder than I expected.

00:09:50.793 --> 00:09:51.858
Impressive.

00:09:51.858 --> 00:09:53.590
I'm not asking for free.

00:09:53.590 --> 00:09:56.013
You've been looking for trout lately, right?

00:09:56.013 --> 00:09:57.456
Trout?

00:10:09.609 --> 00:10:12.902
Raised in pristine valley water,
two generations running the farm,

00:10:12.902 --> 00:10:15.768
HACCP certified.

00:10:16.449 --> 00:10:18.968
Rich, buttery flavor.

00:10:18.968 --> 00:10:22.259
You've tasted it before,
so you know exactly what I mean.

00:10:22.259 --> 00:10:23.832
Have I?

00:10:23.832 --> 00:10:26.652
I'll give you the farm's contact info.

00:10:34.174 --> 00:10:36.147
You're sure about that?

00:10:41.244 --> 00:10:42.801
Go start prepping.

00:10:42.801 --> 00:10:44.704
Yes, Chef.

00:10:45.678 --> 00:10:47.874
Ms. Ui Yeong, impressive.

00:10:47.874 --> 00:10:51.187
How did you even think
to buy cod from a competitor?

00:10:51.187 --> 00:10:53.501
Be glad I could.

00:10:53.501 --> 00:10:57.440
I was about to look into
chartering a boat out to sea.

00:10:58.226 --> 00:10:59.543
You know what?

00:10:59.543 --> 00:11:01.820
She means that.

00:11:01.820 --> 00:11:05.730
You're new here, so you might not know yet.

00:11:05.730 --> 00:11:09.811
But you'll be seeing
a lot more of Ui Yeong in action.

00:11:09.811 --> 00:11:11.400
I'm looking forward to it.

00:11:11.400 --> 00:11:13.926
- Let's get along.
- Yeah.

00:11:15.026 --> 00:11:16.763
You're the best.

00:11:16.763 --> 00:11:19.299
Thank God that worked out.

00:11:22.644 --> 00:11:24.409
Why does the fish smell still not come off?

00:11:24.409 --> 00:11:25.952
- Right?
- Yeah.

00:11:25.952 --> 00:11:27.606
I have a date tonight.

00:11:27.606 --> 00:11:29.219
Look at me.

00:11:29.219 --> 00:11:31.541
"Should I shower first?" Do I smell?

00:11:31.541 --> 00:11:33.001
I feel like I just got intimate with a cod.

00:11:33.001 --> 00:11:34.460
- Do not touch me.
- Seriously?

00:11:34.460 --> 00:11:36.966
- Yes.
- How do I get rid of this smell?

00:11:36.966 --> 00:11:38.960
Gosh.

00:11:38.960 --> 00:11:40.183
You two.

00:11:40.183 --> 00:11:42.279
Come here.

00:11:46.472 --> 00:11:49.266
[Best Employee of the Month]
[Lee Ui Yeong] [Lim Jun Hyuk]

00:11:49.266 --> 00:11:51.323
Do your job, but know your boundaries.

00:11:51.323 --> 00:11:54.240
So you went to our competitor and
advertised that you can't do your job?

00:11:54.240 --> 00:11:56.750
You really think you are that competent?

00:11:56.750 --> 00:11:57.857
You are not.

00:11:57.857 --> 00:12:00.151
If you had properly understood
the client's needs from the start,

00:12:00.151 --> 00:12:02.508
no one would have had to come in
on their day off.

00:12:02.508 --> 00:12:05.321
We are the Purchasing Team,
not fortune-tellers.

00:12:05.321 --> 00:12:08.028
How are we supposed to predict everything?

00:12:08.028 --> 00:12:10.747
If you stay sharp and focused, why can't you?

00:12:10.747 --> 00:12:12.683
It's not like you're dating or married,

00:12:12.683 --> 00:12:14.558
so what else do you have besides work?

00:12:14.558 --> 00:12:16.784
We have plenty to deal with besides work!

00:12:16.784 --> 00:12:17.962
Enough.

00:12:17.962 --> 00:12:19.672
Talking more just wastes my breath.

00:12:19.672 --> 00:12:21.997
Write up a full report on today,
with every receipt attached,

00:12:21.997 --> 00:12:24.375
and have it on my desk by Monday.

00:12:31.225 --> 00:12:33.061
[Purchasing Team]

00:12:35.438 --> 00:12:36.759
[Sorry for being good at my job!]

00:12:38.656 --> 00:12:40.733
It's not like I'm even asking for a thank-you

00:12:40.733 --> 00:12:42.789
[Expense Report]
for fixing it.

00:12:42.789 --> 00:12:44.030
What century are we in?

00:12:44.030 --> 00:12:47.702
Why is she tying our personal lives to work
like it's dried fish on a string?

00:12:47.702 --> 00:12:49.285
Doesn't it get to you?

00:12:49.285 --> 00:12:52.339
Of course it does.
But what am I supposed to do?

00:12:52.339 --> 00:12:55.352
Maybe I should just start dating.

00:12:55.352 --> 00:12:57.105
Want to go on a blind date?

00:12:57.105 --> 00:13:00.671
Let's prove we actually have personal lives.

00:13:00.671 --> 00:13:03.513
I'm not dating just to win an argument.

00:13:03.513 --> 00:13:05.113
If blind dates aren't your thing...

00:13:05.113 --> 00:13:06.385
Want something more casual?

00:13:06.385 --> 00:13:08.568
I've got many options.

00:13:09.486 --> 00:13:11.493
Let's see...

00:13:11.493 --> 00:13:13.133
Here, look.

00:13:13.133 --> 00:13:14.933
What is this?

00:13:19.900 --> 00:13:22.096
Why doesn't he have a face photo?

00:13:22.096 --> 00:13:23.786
What's wrong with that?

00:13:23.786 --> 00:13:25.238
"What's wrong with that?"

00:13:25.238 --> 00:13:27.253
You're going to meet a guy
without seeing his face?

00:13:27.253 --> 00:13:29.470
What if he's a total creep?

00:13:29.470 --> 00:13:30.863
He's got a body.

00:13:30.863 --> 00:13:33.749
Pretty sure a face comes with it.

00:13:35.203 --> 00:13:36.653
Wait, what's this?

00:13:36.653 --> 00:13:39.970
[Faithful to the moment when we're together]
Is that an eggplant... and a peach?

00:13:39.970 --> 00:13:41.653
An eggplant and...

00:13:41.653 --> 00:13:44.250
a peach!

00:13:44.250 --> 00:13:46.529
Oh my God, stop.

00:13:47.149 --> 00:13:49.326
You're going to get yourself in trouble.

00:13:49.326 --> 00:13:51.456
Seriously, stop.

00:13:51.456 --> 00:13:54.568
You hate blind dates. You hate apps.

00:13:54.568 --> 00:13:56.519
You hate everything.

00:13:56.519 --> 00:13:57.585
Do you have someone?

00:13:57.585 --> 00:13:58.757
Have someone?

00:13:58.757 --> 00:14:01.973
See. I'm here working all weekend.

00:14:02.659 --> 00:14:04.513
Fair point.

00:14:11.177 --> 00:14:14.033
[Kang Do Hyun]
Did you sort out what you were busy with?

00:14:16.890 --> 00:14:19.475
Working on it.

00:14:19.475 --> 00:14:22.514
Good. I'm heading to the office
to grab some documents.

00:14:22.514 --> 00:14:25.086
Want to grab dinner?

00:14:25.086 --> 00:14:28.171
There is someone.

00:14:28.171 --> 00:14:30.094
Hyun Min, you said
you had plans tonight, right?

00:14:30.094 --> 00:14:31.679
I'll wrap this up. You can go.

00:14:31.679 --> 00:14:34.349
Oh, really?

00:14:35.276 --> 00:14:38.236
If you don't leave now, I will.

00:14:38.236 --> 00:14:40.313
Ui Yeong, you're the best.

00:14:40.313 --> 00:14:42.902
Here, have this.

00:14:42.902 --> 00:14:44.140
- Bye.
- Bye.

00:14:44.140 --> 00:14:46.950
- I'm leaving.
- Okay.

00:14:46.950 --> 00:14:50.803
This is the reason why
I don't bother with apps or blind dates.

00:14:51.990 --> 00:14:54.256
This is your reward for working all weekend.

00:14:54.256 --> 00:14:56.346
Eat up.

00:14:56.346 --> 00:14:57.371
Thanks.

00:14:57.371 --> 00:14:58.954
It's all thanks to him.

00:14:58.954 --> 00:15:01.204
You don't have to be so formal with me at work.

00:15:01.204 --> 00:15:04.484
You're in Legal.
You're not even technically my junior there.

00:15:04.484 --> 00:15:06.280
I'm trying,

00:15:06.280 --> 00:15:08.411
but it's stuck in my system.

00:15:08.411 --> 00:15:11.131
He is Kang Do Hyun, a year below me in college.

00:15:11.131 --> 00:15:14.008
I heard he became a lawyer after graduation.

00:15:14.008 --> 00:15:15.245
A few months ago,

00:15:15.245 --> 00:15:17.085
he joined our hotel's Legal Team

00:15:17.085 --> 00:15:19.958
as in-house counsel.

00:15:19.958 --> 00:15:21.490
Can I get a napkin?

00:15:25.827 --> 00:15:27.083
What?

00:15:27.083 --> 00:15:30.790
I bought fish at the market earlier.

00:15:30.790 --> 00:15:34.490
I usually wear gloves, but I didn't today.

00:15:34.490 --> 00:15:36.234
- Hey, don't...
- It doesn't smell.

00:15:36.234 --> 00:15:39.816
Just your hand cream. It smells nice.

00:15:41.595 --> 00:15:44.001
We hadn't seen each other
in what feels like half a century,

00:15:44.001 --> 00:15:48.215
and he still has a way
of catching me off guard.

00:15:57.154 --> 00:15:59.974
You look good today.

00:15:59.974 --> 00:16:02.200
Where were you?

00:16:03.894 --> 00:16:05.807
A friend's wedding.

00:16:05.807 --> 00:16:08.851
When they found out
I work at the same company as you,

00:16:08.851 --> 00:16:12.158
they said I must've transferred because of you.

00:16:12.158 --> 00:16:14.618
Oh really?

00:16:14.618 --> 00:16:17.434
Honestly, I was shocked too
when I first saw you at the office.

00:16:17.434 --> 00:16:18.788
You were?

00:16:18.788 --> 00:16:20.932
Yeah. You felt so different,

00:16:20.932 --> 00:16:23.535
I kept staring to make sure it was really you.

00:16:23.535 --> 00:16:26.868
That different?

00:16:27.588 --> 00:16:30.078
They asked if you were still pretty.

00:16:30.078 --> 00:16:32.744
I told them you're exactly the same.

00:16:33.712 --> 00:16:37.212
Why would you encourage that?

00:16:37.212 --> 00:16:38.931
I'm not making it up.

00:16:38.931 --> 00:16:40.934
You are pretty.

00:16:46.160 --> 00:16:48.447
Just eat.

00:16:54.837 --> 00:16:56.121
You too. Eat more.

00:16:56.121 --> 00:16:58.137
Thanks.

00:17:03.776 --> 00:17:06.483
Are you still living up on that hill?

00:17:06.483 --> 00:17:07.976
Yes.

00:17:07.976 --> 00:17:10.056
You remember?

00:17:14.969 --> 00:17:15.993
Get in.

00:17:15.993 --> 00:17:18.095
I'll drive you.

00:17:18.095 --> 00:17:21.015
He said the same thing before.

00:17:22.475 --> 00:17:24.285
- What should we eat?
- Let's get tteokbokki.

00:17:24.285 --> 00:17:26.658
- I know a new place.
- Ui Yeong!

00:17:29.396 --> 00:17:30.427
See you later.

00:17:30.427 --> 00:17:33.633
Back then, Do Hyun didn't have a car.

00:17:33.633 --> 00:17:36.533
He rode a red bike.

00:17:38.793 --> 00:17:40.952
Come on. I'll take you.

00:17:54.129 --> 00:17:56.215
Well...

00:17:56.215 --> 00:18:00.235
My place is up that hill. I'll walk from here.

00:18:02.969 --> 00:18:05.769
Let's go. I'll walk you.

00:18:23.134 --> 00:18:25.365
Thanks. Get home safe.

00:18:25.365 --> 00:18:26.959
Wait!

00:18:26.959 --> 00:18:29.352
I have something to say.

00:18:50.319 --> 00:18:51.564
What are you doing?

00:18:51.564 --> 00:18:53.190
I like you.

00:18:53.190 --> 00:18:55.446
From the first time
I saw you in the student lounge...

00:18:55.446 --> 00:18:56.996
You were all I could see.

00:18:56.996 --> 00:18:58.283
Everything else blurred out.

00:18:58.283 --> 00:19:01.300
Back then, Do Hyun had sincerity.

00:19:01.300 --> 00:19:03.547
- What are you doing? Get up.
- You're really beautiful.

00:19:03.547 --> 00:19:07.114
You could take it easy. But you work so hard.

00:19:07.114 --> 00:19:09.037
You're nothing like girls my age.

00:19:09.037 --> 00:19:11.317
Like most first loves,

00:19:11.317 --> 00:19:14.764
his was rushed and one-sided.

00:19:14.764 --> 00:19:16.114
Please be my girlfriend.

00:19:16.114 --> 00:19:19.010
I'll make you happy. I promise!

00:19:22.445 --> 00:19:24.446
And back then, I...

00:19:24.446 --> 00:19:25.839
I'm sorry.

00:19:25.839 --> 00:19:27.832
I can't.

00:19:31.309 --> 00:19:32.353
Enjoy your meal.

00:19:32.353 --> 00:19:34.509
Just surviving took everything I had.

00:19:34.509 --> 00:19:37.402
Dating was not even on my radar.

00:19:37.402 --> 00:19:39.179
[You have been selected...]
I didn't know what love was,

00:19:39.179 --> 00:19:40.075
[for the 2013 Fall Semester
Academic Scholarship.]

00:19:40.075 --> 00:19:43.589
but I knew I was not ready.

00:19:46.088 --> 00:19:48.472
You say I work hard.

00:19:48.472 --> 00:19:49.772
No.

00:19:49.772 --> 00:19:52.532
I'm fighting to survive.

00:19:52.532 --> 00:19:55.702
There is no room for a relationship in my life.

00:19:56.785 --> 00:19:58.805
But...

00:19:58.805 --> 00:20:00.605
No.

00:20:01.359 --> 00:20:03.541
I'm sorry.

00:20:03.541 --> 00:20:06.308
Let's pretend you never said that.

00:20:37.639 --> 00:20:39.499
The Kang Do Hyun now

00:20:39.499 --> 00:20:42.752
feels like a completely different person.

00:20:49.218 --> 00:20:51.411
Thanks for today.

00:20:51.411 --> 00:20:53.804
Get home safe.

00:20:53.804 --> 00:20:55.864
Ui Yeong.

00:20:55.864 --> 00:20:58.468
Are you seeing anyone these days?

00:20:58.468 --> 00:21:01.728
My friends were curious.

00:21:01.728 --> 00:21:03.315
No, I'm not.

00:21:03.315 --> 00:21:05.028
Why?

00:21:05.028 --> 00:21:07.588
You still not interested in dating?

00:21:07.588 --> 00:21:08.865
Well...

00:21:08.865 --> 00:21:10.825
It's not that.

00:21:10.825 --> 00:21:12.089
I just haven't met anyone.

00:21:12.089 --> 00:21:14.142
It's always work, home, work, home.

00:21:14.142 --> 00:21:16.489
I barely get the chance to meet new people.

00:21:16.489 --> 00:21:18.695
But...

00:21:18.695 --> 00:21:21.445
It doesn't have to be someone new.

00:21:22.339 --> 00:21:23.692
I'm sure

00:21:23.692 --> 00:21:25.958
there's someone good out there.

00:21:27.720 --> 00:21:29.336
Is he...

00:21:29.336 --> 00:21:31.942
talking about himself?

00:21:36.020 --> 00:21:38.813
I'm home.

00:21:38.813 --> 00:21:40.839
Hi, Mom.

00:21:43.654 --> 00:21:46.874
You stormed out earlier,

00:21:46.874 --> 00:21:49.807
and now you're walking in all smiley?

00:22:15.450 --> 00:22:17.424
I've always wondered.

00:22:17.424 --> 00:22:19.917
The office is small, the workload's insane.

00:22:19.917 --> 00:22:22.983
When do people
even find time for situationship?

00:22:25.896 --> 00:22:27.829
People probably don't realize

00:22:27.829 --> 00:22:31.242
we work down in a basement with no sunlight.

00:22:31.242 --> 00:22:34.775
That's why we've got to soak up the sun
whenever we can.

00:22:35.762 --> 00:22:38.449
This feels nice.

00:22:48.667 --> 00:22:51.519
Legal Team's treating today.

00:22:51.519 --> 00:22:54.207
- Wow, thank you.
- Thank you.

00:22:54.207 --> 00:22:56.020
Thank you.

00:22:58.154 --> 00:23:00.324
I like chocolate latte too.

00:23:00.324 --> 00:23:02.147
I'll get you one next time.

00:23:02.147 --> 00:23:04.124
Thanks.

00:23:05.114 --> 00:23:06.964
Thank you.

00:23:06.964 --> 00:23:09.357
But eight hours a day,

00:23:09.357 --> 00:23:12.140
sharing the same conference room,
the same rooftop,

00:23:13.050 --> 00:23:16.113
even the same vending machine...

00:23:16.113 --> 00:23:20.350
The closeness that builds
is stronger than you'd think.

00:23:26.792 --> 00:23:30.001
- So how many...
- Well...

00:23:56.416 --> 00:23:59.383
That was fun back then, right?

00:23:59.383 --> 00:24:01.592
- You've got coffee on you.
- Oh my.

00:24:01.592 --> 00:24:03.792
Again? Thanks.

00:24:03.792 --> 00:24:04.856
Oh, General Manager.

00:24:04.856 --> 00:24:07.645
- Hello.
- Where are you going?

00:24:07.645 --> 00:24:08.847
Just to my office.

00:24:08.847 --> 00:24:09.882
Oh, your office.

00:24:09.882 --> 00:24:11.828
And you? Coffee break?

00:24:11.828 --> 00:24:14.338
Yeah, I'm still half asleep.

00:24:14.338 --> 00:24:15.844
- I see.
- Yeah.

00:24:15.844 --> 00:24:18.677
- Have a good day.
- Oh, right.

00:24:20.424 --> 00:24:22.437
By the way...

00:24:24.517 --> 00:24:27.004
Any chance you'd consider a blind date?

00:24:27.004 --> 00:24:28.029
Sorry?

00:24:28.029 --> 00:24:30.811
You don't have a boyfriend, right?

00:24:30.811 --> 00:24:33.994
There's a young man I volunteer with
at an animal shelter.

00:24:33.994 --> 00:24:36.950
He is very sincere, very upright...

00:24:36.950 --> 00:24:38.118
- And...
- I'm good.

00:24:38.118 --> 00:24:39.203
No, no.

00:24:39.203 --> 00:24:41.691
It's okay. I'm good.

00:24:41.691 --> 00:24:43.378
Blind dates aren't my thing.

00:24:43.378 --> 00:24:46.791
You didn't even pretend to think about it.

00:24:47.526 --> 00:24:49.421
- Okay.
- Yeah.

00:24:49.421 --> 00:24:50.772
Bye.

00:24:50.772 --> 00:24:53.114
- Have a good one.
- Yeah.

00:25:01.455 --> 00:25:05.668
Maybe eighty percent of company loyalty
comes from personal motives.

00:25:11.952 --> 00:25:14.212
I want to go to work.

00:25:15.919 --> 00:25:18.063
You've lost it.

00:25:18.063 --> 00:25:20.504
That flutter could be arrhythmia.

00:25:20.504 --> 00:25:21.954
You had your checkup last year, huh?

00:25:21.954 --> 00:25:24.581
You think I can't tell the difference
between butterflies and being sick?

00:25:24.581 --> 00:25:26.431
You can't.

00:25:26.431 --> 00:25:28.900
Beats me.

00:25:28.900 --> 00:25:30.650
So... Soju and chicken feet again,

00:25:30.650 --> 00:25:32.318
and only for the lady?

00:25:32.318 --> 00:25:34.335
That's right.

00:25:34.335 --> 00:25:37.212
Ma'am, could you microwave this for me?

00:25:37.212 --> 00:25:39.685
Two minutes. Please take the plastic off.

00:25:39.685 --> 00:25:42.118
Endocrine disrupter and all that.

00:25:44.197 --> 00:25:45.534
Only because you're a regular.

00:25:45.534 --> 00:25:47.112
Thank you.

00:25:47.112 --> 00:25:49.552
With eating habits like this,

00:25:49.552 --> 00:25:50.774
how are you two even together?

00:25:50.774 --> 00:25:53.779
- That's too mean!
- We're just friends.

00:25:54.982 --> 00:25:56.869
All right, all right.

00:25:56.869 --> 00:25:59.515
No need to be dramatic.

00:25:59.515 --> 00:26:01.673
- That almost hurt.
- Ma'am, knock on wood.

00:26:01.673 --> 00:26:03.680
I was in a good mood tonight.

00:26:03.680 --> 00:26:04.971
So was I.

00:26:04.971 --> 00:26:06.110
Anything else?

00:26:06.110 --> 00:26:08.303
[We're all someone's treasure.]

00:26:08.303 --> 00:26:09.583
So,

00:26:09.583 --> 00:26:12.023
did Kang Do Hyun ask you out?

00:26:12.023 --> 00:26:14.133
Like I always say, men are simple.

00:26:14.133 --> 00:26:16.663
If they like you, they don't make it confusing.

00:26:16.663 --> 00:26:18.296
It's not confusing.

00:26:18.296 --> 00:26:20.930
There's something I didn't tell you.

00:26:20.930 --> 00:26:23.476
I was... actually...

00:26:23.476 --> 00:26:25.190
his first love.

00:26:25.190 --> 00:26:27.023
What?

00:26:27.742 --> 00:26:31.010
That's pretty powerful.

00:26:31.010 --> 00:26:32.941
He confessed once.

00:26:32.941 --> 00:26:34.062
I turned him down.

00:26:34.062 --> 00:26:36.569
You know how I was in college.

00:26:36.569 --> 00:26:39.171
Dating ranked lower than chicken feet toenails.

00:26:39.171 --> 00:26:42.937
Chicken feet toenails?
That's a visual I didn't need.

00:26:42.937 --> 00:26:44.888
So now that you've got breathing room,

00:26:44.888 --> 00:26:46.940
you're thinking of saying yes?

00:26:49.187 --> 00:26:50.934
But...

00:26:50.934 --> 00:26:53.545
what if he's hesitant

00:26:53.545 --> 00:26:57.113
because I rejected him before?

00:26:58.925 --> 00:27:01.726
Of course that's on his mind.

00:27:01.726 --> 00:27:03.796
Then set the stage.

00:27:03.796 --> 00:27:05.846
Make it easy for him to say it.

00:27:05.846 --> 00:27:07.099
How?

00:27:08.966 --> 00:27:11.129
Create a moment. Just the two of you.

00:27:11.129 --> 00:27:13.411
Like how?

00:27:13.411 --> 00:27:15.479
Grab a drink together.

00:27:15.479 --> 00:27:16.796
Okay.

00:27:16.796 --> 00:27:18.363
Then what should we drink?

00:27:18.363 --> 00:27:20.073
Keep it light with beer?

00:27:20.073 --> 00:27:22.646
Or go honest with soju?

00:27:22.646 --> 00:27:26.513
Here's looking at you, kid.

00:27:31.994 --> 00:27:33.546
Excuse me.

00:27:33.546 --> 00:27:35.911
Are we going all the way
to the source for the inspection?

00:27:35.911 --> 00:27:38.157
Oh, let me explain for you.

00:27:38.157 --> 00:27:40.759
When we first sign a purchase contract,
we visit the supplier.

00:27:40.759 --> 00:27:44.437
After that, it's mostly remote.

00:27:44.437 --> 00:27:47.310
So every now and then, we go check in.

00:27:47.310 --> 00:27:49.621
To make sure
nothing's changed since the contract

00:27:49.621 --> 00:27:51.841
and that we're good to keep working together.

00:27:51.841 --> 00:27:54.051
They're great people, though.

00:27:54.051 --> 00:27:57.138
They always welcome us.

00:27:57.138 --> 00:27:58.698
All right.

00:27:58.698 --> 00:28:01.471
So, who's going to Boseong?

00:28:01.471 --> 00:28:05.038
No one volunteering for the team?

00:28:05.038 --> 00:28:06.214
Well...

00:28:06.214 --> 00:28:07.791
Hyun Min and I

00:28:07.791 --> 00:28:10.148
went to Boseong last year.

00:28:10.148 --> 00:28:11.714
Oh really? Then this year...

00:28:11.714 --> 00:28:14.734
Was it? I thought I went.

00:28:14.734 --> 00:28:17.664
Unfortunately, you two might have to go again.

00:28:17.664 --> 00:28:19.908
My father-in-law's birthday is this weekend.

00:28:19.908 --> 00:28:22.050
Really? Then...

00:28:22.744 --> 00:28:25.964
Wait, wasn't it his birthday last month too?

00:28:25.964 --> 00:28:29.787
How does one person have two birthdays?

00:28:29.787 --> 00:28:32.132
- That's interesting.
- Yeah?

00:28:32.132 --> 00:28:34.168
Oh, not father-in-law.

00:28:34.168 --> 00:28:36.946
My husband's uncle.

00:28:36.946 --> 00:28:38.483
You wouldn't know because you're not married.

00:28:38.483 --> 00:28:40.152
You have to keep track of all that.

00:28:40.152 --> 00:28:42.593
Anyway, I need to stop by Mapo to shop,

00:28:42.593 --> 00:28:45.668
so the route works better that way.

00:28:45.668 --> 00:28:46.925
Honestly, whoever goes,

00:28:46.925 --> 00:28:49.437
the Mapo route works just fine.

00:28:49.437 --> 00:28:51.765
That's enough.

00:28:51.765 --> 00:28:54.355
She's got lots of family stuff going on,
so you two just go.

00:28:54.355 --> 00:28:55.502
It won't take long.

00:28:55.502 --> 00:28:57.941
- But...
- What?

00:29:00.297 --> 00:29:02.674
Why?

00:29:02.674 --> 00:29:03.532
[Vendor Site Visit Schedule]

00:29:03.532 --> 00:29:06.280
[Boseong Tea Fields]
[Lee Ui Yeong, Jung Hyun Min]

00:29:07.262 --> 00:29:09.097
Let's make this the last year.

00:29:09.097 --> 00:29:12.352
Next year, I'll find a way out of it.

00:29:13.143 --> 00:29:14.853
Sae Byeok, what about you?

00:29:14.853 --> 00:29:17.820
I'll go with you to Boseong.

00:29:17.820 --> 00:29:19.324
I looked it up earlier,

00:29:19.324 --> 00:29:21.122
and they film movies in the tea fields.

00:29:21.122 --> 00:29:23.446
It's even a popular date spot.

00:29:23.446 --> 00:29:25.447
Yeah?

00:29:25.447 --> 00:29:27.958
We're going there to work.

00:29:27.958 --> 00:29:29.883
We're not sightseeing.

00:29:29.883 --> 00:29:31.740
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:29:31.740 --> 00:29:34.417
Hey, no need to apologize.
Work can have some fun in it.

00:29:34.417 --> 00:29:37.395
After the inspection, let's look around a bit.

00:29:37.395 --> 00:29:39.596
Sounds good.

00:29:42.714 --> 00:29:44.473
[Boseong Tea Fields]
[Lee Ui Yeong, Jung Hyun Min, Sim Sae Byeok]

00:29:44.473 --> 00:29:46.483
I'll take care of it.

00:29:50.059 --> 00:29:53.945
Can we talk in the break room
after your meeting?

00:29:55.425 --> 00:29:57.536
Hyun Min, can you handle this for me?

00:29:57.536 --> 00:29:59.844
- Sure.
- Just a moment.

00:30:00.539 --> 00:30:02.638
Let's go.

00:30:11.636 --> 00:30:13.383
Is something wrong?

00:30:13.383 --> 00:30:14.646
No.

00:30:14.646 --> 00:30:17.222
Nothing like that.

00:30:19.310 --> 00:30:20.954
Can I tag along

00:30:20.954 --> 00:30:22.680
on the Purchasing Team inspection?

00:30:22.680 --> 00:30:24.135
You?

00:30:24.135 --> 00:30:27.117
Why would you go on an inspection?

00:30:27.117 --> 00:30:30.095
I figured I should see it firsthand
at least once.

00:30:30.095 --> 00:30:32.151
Get to know the vendor.

00:30:32.151 --> 00:30:34.521
Besides, lawyers are often out in the field.

00:30:34.521 --> 00:30:36.518
Oh, really?

00:30:36.518 --> 00:30:37.582
Okay, then.

00:30:37.582 --> 00:30:39.666
I'll let Manager Na Ri know.

00:30:39.666 --> 00:30:41.155
Make time this weekend and head to Mapo.

00:30:41.155 --> 00:30:43.798
Actually, Boseong.

00:30:43.798 --> 00:30:46.791
I'll go with you.

00:30:46.791 --> 00:30:49.404
You want to go all the way to Boseong?

00:30:49.404 --> 00:30:51.461
That's really far.

00:30:51.461 --> 00:30:53.890
It's an overnight trip. You okay with that?

00:30:53.890 --> 00:30:55.031
I know.

00:30:55.031 --> 00:30:56.985
That's why I'm going.

00:30:56.985 --> 00:31:00.558
I've got a few things I want to ask in person.

00:31:01.494 --> 00:31:03.124
Then set the stage.

00:31:03.124 --> 00:31:04.799
Make it easy for him to say it.

00:31:04.799 --> 00:31:07.587
It's even a popular date spot.

00:31:08.861 --> 00:31:12.340
That's when I got a feeling.

00:31:12.340 --> 00:31:14.581
Is it going to be awkward?

00:31:14.581 --> 00:31:15.758
That feeling...

00:31:15.758 --> 00:31:19.001
like that day would be our first day.

00:31:19.001 --> 00:31:20.588
No.

00:31:20.588 --> 00:31:22.245
Yeah. Come.

00:31:22.245 --> 00:31:24.441
It's fine.

00:31:59.298 --> 00:32:00.476
Nice.

00:32:00.476 --> 00:32:02.638
Not bad.

00:32:05.423 --> 00:32:07.073
I'm heading out.

00:32:07.073 --> 00:32:08.985
- Where are you going?
- I've got an inspection.

00:32:08.985 --> 00:32:11.141
I'm staying over and coming back tomorrow.

00:32:11.141 --> 00:32:12.179
Mom.

00:32:12.179 --> 00:32:14.083
From now on,
if someone gives you a wedding invite,

00:32:14.083 --> 00:32:16.449
- Just go.
- What?

00:32:17.289 --> 00:32:19.019
Go to the wedding.

00:32:19.019 --> 00:32:21.935
I think it's okay now.

00:32:21.935 --> 00:32:23.306
I'll be back.

00:32:23.306 --> 00:32:25.289
What is she even talking about all of a sudden?

00:32:25.289 --> 00:32:28.488
- Have a good trip.
- Okay.

00:32:39.481 --> 00:32:40.878
- Ui Yeong.
- Hey.

00:32:40.878 --> 00:32:43.770
- Let me take that.
- Thanks.

00:32:43.770 --> 00:32:44.875
Ui Yeong!

00:32:44.875 --> 00:32:46.371
Hey.

00:32:46.371 --> 00:32:48.709
I can't believe I'm going to Boseong again!

00:32:48.709 --> 00:32:50.193
You're going again!

00:32:50.193 --> 00:32:52.267
I can't make my feet move!

00:32:52.267 --> 00:32:54.330
Hurry up.

00:33:10.880 --> 00:33:13.844
- You okay?
- I'm fine.

00:33:19.628 --> 00:33:22.229
The weather's nice.

00:33:33.030 --> 00:33:36.317
We're here.

00:33:38.700 --> 00:33:39.997
Hello.

00:33:39.997 --> 00:33:42.350
- Hello.
- Welcome.

00:33:42.350 --> 00:33:44.708
Thank you for coming all this way.

00:33:44.708 --> 00:33:46.293
These are pastries from our hotel.

00:33:46.293 --> 00:33:47.858
Please share them with the staff.

00:33:47.858 --> 00:33:50.778
Oh my, thank you.

00:33:50.778 --> 00:33:53.035
We'll be enjoying these.

00:33:53.035 --> 00:33:54.652
Since we're short on time,

00:33:54.652 --> 00:33:57.452
why don't you drop your bags first
and start the inspection?

00:33:57.452 --> 00:33:58.957
- Sure.
- Okay.

00:33:58.957 --> 00:34:02.057
- Please show them this way.
- I'll help you.

00:34:03.816 --> 00:34:04.893
Ui Yeong,

00:34:04.893 --> 00:34:07.976
doesn't Attorney Kang seem a little suspicious?

00:34:07.976 --> 00:34:09.769
What? Why?

00:34:09.769 --> 00:34:11.319
Think about it.

00:34:11.319 --> 00:34:13.660
Why would he come all the way out here?

00:34:13.660 --> 00:34:16.166
And he's carrying all the bags himself.

00:34:16.887 --> 00:34:18.651
He's here to work.

00:34:18.651 --> 00:34:20.074
You might not know this,

00:34:20.074 --> 00:34:22.874
but lawyers go on inspections all the time.

00:34:24.734 --> 00:34:27.658
Wait, why are you defending him?

00:34:27.658 --> 00:34:29.677
Something smells off.

00:34:31.158 --> 00:34:33.077
I'm wearing perfume.

00:34:33.077 --> 00:34:35.434
What? Why are you wearing perfume?

00:34:35.434 --> 00:34:38.460
- Hurry up.
- Hey!

00:34:40.538 --> 00:34:42.889
For the inspection, let's split into two teams.

00:34:42.889 --> 00:34:46.703
One to the tea fields
and one to the processing plant.

00:34:46.703 --> 00:34:49.866
Then we'll all have dinner together tonight.

00:34:49.866 --> 00:34:50.555
Sounds good.

00:34:50.555 --> 00:34:52.283
How should we divide up?

00:34:52.283 --> 00:34:54.502
I'll go to the tea fields.

00:34:54.502 --> 00:34:57.860
I'll head to the processing plant.

00:34:57.860 --> 00:34:59.989
I'll go to the tea fields too.

00:34:59.989 --> 00:35:01.887
Then the gentleman will go to the plant?

00:35:01.887 --> 00:35:04.217
If possible,

00:35:04.217 --> 00:35:06.857
I'd like to go to the tea fields as well.

00:35:06.857 --> 00:35:08.830
Would that be okay?

00:35:08.830 --> 00:35:10.850
Oh, sure.

00:35:10.850 --> 00:35:12.392
That's probably why you came, right?

00:35:12.392 --> 00:35:13.902
Go ahead.

00:35:13.902 --> 00:35:15.299
All right. Let's move.

00:35:15.299 --> 00:35:17.457
- Yes.
- Everyone, this way.

00:35:17.457 --> 00:35:18.928
- Let's get going.
- Okay.

00:35:18.928 --> 00:35:21.285
- This way.
- See you later.

00:35:21.285 --> 00:35:24.058
- Let's go.
- Have a safe trip.

00:35:29.848 --> 00:35:31.692
Boseong is

00:35:31.692 --> 00:35:33.919
the oldest and largest

00:35:33.919 --> 00:35:36.799
tea-producing region in Korea.

00:35:36.799 --> 00:35:39.016
These lush tea fields were

00:35:39.016 --> 00:35:40.600
even named one of CNN's

00:35:40.600 --> 00:35:44.853
most stunning landscapes in the world.

00:35:46.414 --> 00:35:47.971
If you got to see this every day,

00:35:47.971 --> 00:35:49.824
I think you'd feel so at peace.

00:35:49.824 --> 00:35:51.377
I know.

00:35:51.377 --> 00:35:55.344
They really take such good care of it.

00:36:00.889 --> 00:36:03.102
Smell the aroma.

00:36:04.063 --> 00:36:06.942
Sae Byeok, smell this.

00:36:08.282 --> 00:36:10.836
- Nice, right?
- It is.

00:36:24.069 --> 00:36:28.439
When you build the fields in terraces
along the mountain slope like this,

00:36:28.439 --> 00:36:30.490
the tea plants get even sunlight,

00:36:30.490 --> 00:36:32.559
- which produces higher-quality tea.
- It's hot.

00:36:32.559 --> 00:36:34.479
Even the leftover leaves after harvest...

00:36:34.479 --> 00:36:37.082
Ui Yeong, have some water.

00:36:37.082 --> 00:36:38.989
Thanks.

00:36:40.205 --> 00:36:42.469
Walking like this with you

00:36:42.469 --> 00:36:44.882
kind of feels like we're back in college.

00:36:44.882 --> 00:36:46.955
It does.

00:36:49.367 --> 00:36:50.907
Ui Yeong,

00:36:50.907 --> 00:36:53.233
later tonight,

00:36:53.947 --> 00:36:56.196
can we talk for a minute? Just the two of us?

00:36:59.167 --> 00:37:01.666
Yes, sure.

00:37:14.710 --> 00:37:16.783
So tired.

00:37:18.470 --> 00:37:20.914
There were no issues at the processing plant.

00:37:20.914 --> 00:37:23.004
The workflow matched the documents,

00:37:23.004 --> 00:37:27.517
and I checked
the recent sanitation inspection report.

00:37:27.517 --> 00:37:29.271
The tea fields

00:37:29.271 --> 00:37:31.497
looked great too.

00:37:35.332 --> 00:37:37.382
What was so great?

00:37:37.382 --> 00:37:40.789
Why are you looking at that
like it's a love story?

00:37:40.789 --> 00:37:43.122
It's a photo Attorney Kang took.

00:37:46.084 --> 00:37:48.509
Men's dating skills are still the same.

00:37:48.509 --> 00:37:50.472
This is that move, right?

00:37:50.472 --> 00:37:52.745
Take pictures of everyone
just to get one good shot

00:37:52.745 --> 00:37:54.250
of the person you like.

00:37:54.250 --> 00:37:56.232
You know?

00:37:56.232 --> 00:37:58.125
Is that what it is?

00:38:01.025 --> 00:38:02.669
So since when?

00:38:02.669 --> 00:38:05.058
Legal and Purchasing Team

00:38:05.058 --> 00:38:07.818
don't exactly overlap that much.

00:38:07.818 --> 00:38:09.095
Actually...

00:38:09.095 --> 00:38:10.519
We've known each other for a while.

00:38:10.519 --> 00:38:12.357
He was my junior in college.

00:38:12.357 --> 00:38:13.976
No way.

00:38:13.976 --> 00:38:16.431
There's history?

00:38:16.431 --> 00:38:17.455
Okay.

00:38:17.455 --> 00:38:19.854
That's a well-aged connection.

00:38:21.670 --> 00:38:22.768
Ui Yeong.

00:38:22.768 --> 00:38:25.481
So what if Attorney Kang asks you out?

00:38:25.481 --> 00:38:28.008
What would you do?

00:38:28.008 --> 00:38:30.634
Would office dating be okay?

00:38:33.046 --> 00:38:36.159
If that ever happened,

00:38:36.159 --> 00:38:39.099
I'd make sure it doesn't affect work.

00:38:41.830 --> 00:38:43.441
You're already way too far ahead.

00:38:43.441 --> 00:38:44.828
No, I'm not.

00:38:44.828 --> 00:38:46.019
Okay.

00:38:46.019 --> 00:38:47.791
Got it.

00:38:47.791 --> 00:38:50.418
Then if you don't come back tonight,
I'll pretend I didn't notice.

00:38:50.418 --> 00:38:52.222
Why are you jumping to conclusions?

00:38:52.222 --> 00:38:54.718
It's not like that.

00:38:54.718 --> 00:38:55.948
Sure seems like it.

00:38:55.948 --> 00:38:57.894
They're calling us for dinner.

00:38:57.894 --> 00:39:00.023
Okay, I'm coming.

00:39:01.875 --> 00:39:04.961
You're walking pretty lightly there.

00:39:06.961 --> 00:39:09.098
Good work today.

00:39:09.098 --> 00:39:11.441
- Thank you.
- Good work.

00:39:11.441 --> 00:39:15.535
You all worked hard today.

00:39:15.535 --> 00:39:18.716
Let's hear a few words from Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:39:18.716 --> 00:39:22.774
Thank you so much for helping us
complete the inspection today.

00:39:22.774 --> 00:39:24.051
We'll make sure

00:39:24.051 --> 00:39:26.255
your hard work pays off when we get back.

00:39:26.255 --> 00:39:27.668
And...

00:39:27.668 --> 00:39:29.801
Please come visit our hotel sometime.

00:39:29.801 --> 00:39:32.139
We'll take great care of you.

00:39:32.727 --> 00:39:34.641
All right, let's make a toast.

00:39:34.641 --> 00:39:36.065
- Cheers.
- Yeah.

00:39:36.065 --> 00:39:39.325
- Great work, everyone.
- Great work.

00:39:40.994 --> 00:39:43.741
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:39:43.741 --> 00:39:45.072
By the way,

00:39:45.072 --> 00:39:47.347
can I ask you something?

00:39:47.347 --> 00:39:48.444
Are you single?

00:39:48.444 --> 00:39:49.994
- Sorry?
- Are you married?

00:39:51.467 --> 00:39:53.599
Well... I don't even have a boyfriend.

00:39:53.599 --> 00:39:55.136
Spending a beautiful weekend

00:39:55.136 --> 00:39:57.310
with a bunch of old folks like us.

00:39:57.310 --> 00:39:59.923
No wonder you're single.

00:39:59.923 --> 00:40:03.810
Honestly, it feels like I'm visiting family.

00:40:03.810 --> 00:40:05.880
She is pretty and sweet.

00:40:05.880 --> 00:40:08.643
- Eat up.
- Thank you.

00:40:10.427 --> 00:40:11.984
Have a drink with me.

00:40:11.984 --> 00:40:13.861
Oh, stop it.

00:40:14.507 --> 00:40:16.373
What?

00:40:18.640 --> 00:40:20.268
- The food was amazing.
- Eat more.

00:40:20.268 --> 00:40:22.117
- I ate plenty.
- Bring another bottle.

00:40:22.117 --> 00:40:25.370
Goodness, not that much.

00:40:26.510 --> 00:40:28.676
I'm so full.

00:40:28.676 --> 00:40:30.030
- Ui Yeong.
- Yes?

00:40:30.030 --> 00:40:32.091
Want to take a short walk?

00:40:32.091 --> 00:40:34.047
Yeah. Okay.

00:40:37.194 --> 00:40:39.354
I love it here.

00:40:58.317 --> 00:40:59.783
Careful. You okay?

00:40:59.783 --> 00:41:02.089
Yeah, I'm fine.

00:41:03.445 --> 00:41:05.245
Let's go.

00:41:19.342 --> 00:41:21.729
Sit here.

00:41:38.065 --> 00:41:39.771
So?

00:41:39.771 --> 00:41:43.278
Now that you've seen the inspection,
what do you think?

00:41:43.278 --> 00:41:45.078
It's nice.

00:41:46.390 --> 00:41:49.750
But I've had something else on my mind.

00:41:53.921 --> 00:41:56.300
Actually...

00:41:57.609 --> 00:42:00.455
I didn't come to Boseong for work.

00:42:00.455 --> 00:42:02.255
What?

00:42:03.157 --> 00:42:04.957
Then why?

00:42:07.551 --> 00:42:11.257
I don't know how this will sound...

00:42:11.257 --> 00:42:13.000
but even when I was studying for the bar

00:42:13.000 --> 00:42:15.271
after graduation,

00:42:15.271 --> 00:42:17.823
I used to think about you.

00:42:19.117 --> 00:42:20.877
Me?

00:42:20.877 --> 00:42:23.077
You did?

00:42:25.508 --> 00:42:28.495
I wondered what kind of guy you'd end up with.

00:42:28.495 --> 00:42:31.881
How great he must be.

00:42:33.834 --> 00:42:35.725
After you turned me down,

00:42:35.725 --> 00:42:38.398
I had a hard time for a while.

00:42:39.408 --> 00:42:41.707
I didn't know that.

00:42:43.414 --> 00:42:46.071
But getting rejected helped me

00:42:46.071 --> 00:42:49.334
figure out where I stood.

00:42:49.953 --> 00:42:52.736
So I worked like crazy and became a lawyer.

00:42:52.736 --> 00:42:54.966
I wanted

00:42:54.966 --> 00:42:57.412
to become someone
anyone would be proud to like.

00:42:58.126 --> 00:42:59.872
No.

00:42:59.872 --> 00:43:03.086
You were already
more than good enough back then.

00:43:03.086 --> 00:43:05.012
I just wasn't in a place to date.

00:43:05.012 --> 00:43:07.566
That's why I said no.

00:43:07.566 --> 00:43:10.852
You don't have to make it better.

00:43:10.852 --> 00:43:14.112
I'm over it now.

00:43:27.276 --> 00:43:30.589
I told you I had something to ask. Right?

00:43:34.970 --> 00:43:36.620
What do you think

00:43:36.620 --> 00:43:39.353
about office dating?

00:43:44.689 --> 00:43:47.969
Of course, it's not easy.

00:43:48.715 --> 00:43:50.266
People would be watching.

00:43:50.266 --> 00:43:52.775
There'd be a lot of talk, too...

00:43:52.775 --> 00:43:53.936
And...

00:43:53.936 --> 00:43:56.736
you'd have to work even harder.

00:43:58.968 --> 00:44:00.774
But

00:44:02.741 --> 00:44:06.019
if you really like someone,

00:44:06.019 --> 00:44:09.513
don't you go in knowing all that?

00:44:10.547 --> 00:44:14.299
You can't exactly stop yourself
from liking someone.

00:44:15.373 --> 00:44:17.919
You really think that?

00:44:23.703 --> 00:44:25.503
Then,

00:44:27.079 --> 00:44:29.032
could you

00:44:32.106 --> 00:44:35.672
help me talk to Sae Byeok? Just the two of us?

00:44:36.486 --> 00:44:37.716
What?

00:44:37.716 --> 00:44:40.376
Sae Byeok?

00:44:40.376 --> 00:44:42.173
Why?

00:44:42.173 --> 00:44:45.373
I'm planning to confess to her tonight.

00:44:46.080 --> 00:44:48.566
What?

00:44:48.566 --> 00:44:51.993
We barely run into each other at work.

00:44:51.993 --> 00:44:54.017
We're not even in the same department.

00:44:54.017 --> 00:44:56.506
And she's just an intern.

00:44:56.506 --> 00:44:59.499
I kept trying to read the room,

00:45:00.353 --> 00:45:03.206
and somehow weeks have already gone by.

00:45:04.566 --> 00:45:06.553
- Hello.
- Here.

00:45:06.553 --> 00:45:08.759
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:45:18.232 --> 00:45:19.516
Thank you.

00:45:19.516 --> 00:45:22.085
Thanks for the coffee.

00:45:44.633 --> 00:45:45.741
[Boseong Tea Fields]
[Lee Ui Yeong, Jung Hyun Min...]

00:45:45.741 --> 00:45:46.895
[Sim Sae Byeok]

00:45:48.496 --> 00:45:50.548
So tired.

00:45:58.141 --> 00:45:59.165
Oh, right.

00:45:59.165 --> 00:46:02.141
It's cute when she tries so hard

00:46:02.141 --> 00:46:03.572
without knowing all the tricks.

00:46:03.572 --> 00:46:05.685
It's impressive.

00:46:06.408 --> 00:46:08.894
When we get back,

00:46:08.894 --> 00:46:09.974
like this,

00:46:09.974 --> 00:46:12.078
I'll send you a wink.

00:46:12.078 --> 00:46:14.022
You stall a little

00:46:14.022 --> 00:46:16.046
and send Sae Byeok over here.

00:46:16.046 --> 00:46:19.912
I'll come ahead and get things ready.

00:46:21.727 --> 00:46:24.986
How can love change like that...

00:46:26.027 --> 00:46:27.650
If it's not too much trouble,

00:46:27.650 --> 00:46:30.233
can you come with me?

00:46:31.502 --> 00:46:33.439
Don't drink too late.

00:46:33.439 --> 00:46:35.101
You have a long drive tomorrow.

00:46:35.101 --> 00:46:38.522
Yes, thank you. Thank you for cooking.

00:46:46.123 --> 00:46:47.326
Here you go.

00:46:47.326 --> 00:46:48.829
Attention, everyone.

00:46:48.829 --> 00:46:50.346
How about a game?

00:46:50.346 --> 00:46:51.789
Attorney Kang, come over here.

00:46:51.789 --> 00:46:53.493
Sae Byeok, you too.

00:46:53.493 --> 00:46:55.769
- Let's play.
- Okay.

00:46:55.769 --> 00:46:58.666
Put the soju down.

00:46:58.666 --> 00:46:59.873
So...

00:46:59.873 --> 00:47:01.260
Let's play

00:47:01.260 --> 00:47:02.903
"Truth Game."

00:47:02.903 --> 00:47:04.062
Simple rules.

00:47:04.062 --> 00:47:05.297
Only tell the truth.

00:47:05.297 --> 00:47:07.993
Be honest. Be sincere.

00:47:07.993 --> 00:47:09.858
If you say no comment,

00:47:09.858 --> 00:47:13.219
you pay with a shot.

00:47:22.297 --> 00:47:24.662
Why me?

00:47:24.662 --> 00:47:27.595
Attorney Kang, why are you really here?

00:47:29.805 --> 00:47:32.005
For work.

00:47:32.005 --> 00:47:34.875
We just said truth only.

00:47:34.875 --> 00:47:37.259
You came all the way out here.

00:47:37.259 --> 00:47:38.964
Didn't you cross mountains and rivers

00:47:38.964 --> 00:47:41.155
to follow someone you like?

00:47:41.155 --> 00:47:42.350
Jung Hyun Min,

00:47:42.350 --> 00:47:43.374
Stop.

00:47:43.374 --> 00:47:45.606
Hold on.

00:47:46.607 --> 00:47:48.549
The person Attorney Kang likes...

00:47:48.549 --> 00:47:51.397
No, his ideal type...

00:47:51.397 --> 00:47:53.331
She's sitting right here, isn't she?

00:47:53.331 --> 00:47:55.941
With that sweet, innocent face,

00:47:55.941 --> 00:47:58.434
and totally competent at work.

00:47:58.434 --> 00:48:01.315
That's Lee Ui Yeong, right?

00:48:05.336 --> 00:48:07.389
What?

00:48:10.219 --> 00:48:12.676
I've never liked someone
like that before in my life.

00:48:12.676 --> 00:48:14.009
Please be my girlfriend.

00:48:14.009 --> 00:48:16.815
I'll make you really happy.

00:48:17.409 --> 00:48:18.693
Right.

00:48:18.693 --> 00:48:20.159
He did say

00:48:20.159 --> 00:48:23.003
I was his first love.

00:48:23.003 --> 00:48:24.206
Love may change,

00:48:24.206 --> 00:48:27.050
but your first love stays with you.

00:48:27.050 --> 00:48:30.209
Ui Yeong is a great person.

00:48:30.209 --> 00:48:31.258
But

00:48:31.258 --> 00:48:34.889
that doesn't mean I want to date her.

00:48:34.889 --> 00:48:38.629
And she's older than me.

00:48:39.434 --> 00:48:41.710
What?

00:48:41.710 --> 00:48:43.593
Aren't you only a year apart?

00:48:43.593 --> 00:48:44.902
When's your birthday?

00:48:44.902 --> 00:48:46.723
No, I just...

00:48:46.723 --> 00:48:48.630
That's how I feel.

00:48:48.630 --> 00:48:50.700
It's my preference.

00:48:50.700 --> 00:48:53.373
Please respect that.

00:48:56.636 --> 00:48:58.436
And...

00:49:03.019 --> 00:49:06.332
There's someone else I like.

00:49:11.088 --> 00:49:13.308
Sae Byeok.

00:49:18.767 --> 00:49:21.840
I didn't think I'd end up saying it like this,

00:49:24.905 --> 00:49:27.951
but when I look at you,

00:49:29.041 --> 00:49:32.820
these pure feelings I forgot I had

00:49:33.514 --> 00:49:36.794
come back to life.

00:49:39.014 --> 00:49:41.014
Would you

00:49:41.014 --> 00:49:43.467
accept how I feel?

00:50:23.871 --> 00:50:26.418
[Walking Trail - Slippery When Wet]

00:50:27.003 --> 00:50:28.393
Lee Ui Yeong, seriously.

00:50:28.393 --> 00:50:30.443
Even if it's been a while,

00:50:30.443 --> 00:50:33.133
how do you fumble that badly?

00:50:33.133 --> 00:50:35.157
This is insane.

00:50:35.157 --> 00:50:37.902
So embarrassed.

00:50:37.902 --> 00:50:40.121
How am I supposed to show my face now?

00:50:40.121 --> 00:50:42.138
Just because I haven't dated in a few years,

00:50:42.138 --> 00:50:44.850
I lose all my instincts?

00:50:44.850 --> 00:50:46.040
I've officially lost it.

00:50:46.040 --> 00:50:48.616
[No Entry]
Completely lost it.

00:50:57.785 --> 00:51:00.291
Where am I?

00:51:54.898 --> 00:51:55.922
Who's there?

00:51:55.922 --> 00:51:58.324
Help!

00:52:00.467 --> 00:52:02.874
Ms. Lee Ui Yeong?

00:52:04.973 --> 00:52:07.689
What are you doing out here?

00:52:07.689 --> 00:52:09.808
Oh, Ma'am...

00:52:24.659 --> 00:52:26.273
On your way up,

00:52:26.273 --> 00:52:29.559
didn't you see the No Entry sign?

00:52:30.238 --> 00:52:34.978
It's a thirty-minute hike from the lodging.

00:52:34.978 --> 00:52:37.002
I just felt a little suffocated.

00:52:37.002 --> 00:52:39.578
I kept walking without thinking.

00:52:39.578 --> 00:52:43.042
You were running straight ahead.

00:52:43.042 --> 00:52:46.742
I thought you were some injured wild animal.

00:52:49.857 --> 00:52:51.300
Oh dear,

00:52:51.300 --> 00:52:53.490
you're all scratched up.

00:52:53.490 --> 00:52:56.200
Drink this slowly and rest for a bit.

00:52:56.200 --> 00:52:58.770
I'll put some ointment on it.

00:52:59.679 --> 00:53:01.698
Go on, drink.

00:53:03.059 --> 00:53:05.525
Thank you.

00:53:08.008 --> 00:53:10.481
Here.

00:53:22.045 --> 00:53:24.618
- Ma'am.
- Yes?

00:53:24.618 --> 00:53:27.157
That tea...

00:53:27.157 --> 00:53:30.671
You leave it aged on purpose, right?

00:53:31.640 --> 00:53:35.493
Tea gets better with time.

00:53:35.493 --> 00:53:38.440
Unlike people.

00:53:38.440 --> 00:53:40.433
Right?

00:53:43.885 --> 00:53:46.519
Oh, this?

00:53:46.519 --> 00:53:47.682
No,

00:53:47.682 --> 00:53:49.919
I just haven't gotten around to sorting it.

00:53:49.919 --> 00:53:54.132
Half of this will probably get tossed.

00:53:55.499 --> 00:53:57.686
Why?

00:53:57.686 --> 00:53:58.942
Doesn't tea

00:53:58.942 --> 00:54:02.029
get richer the longer it ages?

00:54:02.029 --> 00:54:04.179
Depends on the tea,

00:54:04.179 --> 00:54:07.346
but generally, no.

00:54:07.346 --> 00:54:08.887
The aroma fades.

00:54:08.887 --> 00:54:12.215
The flavor weakens.

00:54:12.215 --> 00:54:16.156
Every year, new tender leaves grow.

00:54:16.156 --> 00:54:19.655
Why hold on to the old ones?

00:54:20.436 --> 00:54:21.900
Tea or anything else,

00:54:21.900 --> 00:54:26.325
once it gets too old, it loses its value.

00:54:36.715 --> 00:54:39.761
It loses...

00:54:40.902 --> 00:54:42.889
its value.

00:54:42.889 --> 00:54:45.842
I always thought that whenever I decided to,

00:54:45.842 --> 00:54:47.646
I could fall in love.

00:54:47.646 --> 00:54:50.425
Date. Love. Anytime.

00:54:50.425 --> 00:54:51.706
But

00:54:51.706 --> 00:54:54.099
I was wrong.

00:54:54.779 --> 00:54:56.432
I let

00:54:56.432 --> 00:54:58.603
the best years to love

00:54:58.603 --> 00:55:00.836
just pass me by.

00:55:10.655 --> 00:55:12.774
Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:55:15.115 --> 00:55:17.495
Are you crying?

00:55:17.495 --> 00:55:19.748
Oh...

00:55:19.748 --> 00:55:23.218
Is tea really that sad?

00:55:25.328 --> 00:55:28.247
It is.

00:55:28.247 --> 00:55:31.271
Then what happens to the old leaves?

00:55:31.271 --> 00:55:33.513
I thought they were finally starting to deepen.

00:55:33.513 --> 00:55:36.285
If they don't even become good tea,

00:55:36.285 --> 00:55:39.538
where do they go?

00:55:40.476 --> 00:55:42.939
Oh dear.

00:55:42.939 --> 00:55:45.484
Oh my.

00:55:45.484 --> 00:55:47.517
Oh...

00:55:48.746 --> 00:55:51.103
All right.

00:55:51.103 --> 00:55:52.782
Go ahead and cry.

00:55:52.782 --> 00:55:55.128
Let it out.

00:55:55.128 --> 00:55:57.802
If you need to cry, then cry.

00:56:42.078 --> 00:56:44.924
- Hello.
- Good morning.

00:56:45.645 --> 00:56:48.111
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thanks.

00:56:51.127 --> 00:56:52.433
Oh gosh.

00:56:52.433 --> 00:56:55.225
The sun's strong today.

00:56:55.225 --> 00:56:58.264
Better reapply sunscreen.

00:57:00.268 --> 00:57:02.955
Enjoy your food, Ui Yeong.

00:57:14.042 --> 00:57:16.586
Ui Yeong.

00:57:16.586 --> 00:57:18.076
Weren't you supposed to help me?

00:57:18.076 --> 00:57:20.886
Why did you suddenly leave last night?

00:57:20.886 --> 00:57:23.686
I drank too much.

00:57:24.760 --> 00:57:27.853
Why are you grabbing my wrist like that?

00:57:27.853 --> 00:57:30.506
You're way too casual.

00:57:43.755 --> 00:57:45.353
Am I the only one getting older?

00:57:45.353 --> 00:57:46.765
He's aging too.

00:57:46.765 --> 00:57:49.274
Dating an older woman is thrilling at twenty.

00:57:49.274 --> 00:57:51.042
Guess once the woman is older, not so much.

00:57:51.042 --> 00:57:52.159
Hey.

00:57:52.159 --> 00:57:54.052
I never believed that whole

00:57:54.052 --> 00:57:57.279
"women hit thirty and it's over" thing.

00:57:57.279 --> 00:57:58.876
But now

00:57:58.876 --> 00:58:00.949
I get it.

00:58:02.205 --> 00:58:05.736
It's not like someone points at you
and says you've lost value.

00:58:05.736 --> 00:58:07.167
You just...

00:58:07.167 --> 00:58:09.403
quietly...

00:58:09.403 --> 00:58:12.167
get pushed out of the frame.

00:58:12.167 --> 00:58:16.553
A lot of people don't think that way.

00:58:16.553 --> 00:58:18.986
I'm fine.

00:58:18.986 --> 00:58:20.764
Besides, I'm not into guys

00:58:20.764 --> 00:58:22.516
who won't date older women anyway.

00:58:22.516 --> 00:58:23.853
But...

00:58:23.853 --> 00:58:25.560
It's just... my heart.

00:58:25.560 --> 00:58:28.438
I wanted to care about someone.

00:58:28.438 --> 00:58:32.135
To think about someone.

00:58:32.135 --> 00:58:35.281
And now it feels like that part of me
has nowhere to go.

00:58:37.182 --> 00:58:38.801
That's what makes me sad.

00:58:38.801 --> 00:58:41.315
Kang Do Hyun, that jerk.

00:58:48.662 --> 00:58:51.385
So what if he doesn't see you
as dating material?

00:58:51.385 --> 00:58:53.225
Does that mean you give up on love?

00:58:53.225 --> 00:58:55.965
Well... no.

00:58:56.842 --> 00:58:57.556
It doesn't.

00:58:57.556 --> 00:58:59.516
Then find someone new.

00:58:59.516 --> 00:59:01.221
There are dating apps.

00:59:01.221 --> 00:59:02.812
I hate those.

00:59:02.812 --> 00:59:04.979
Okay. Then go on blind dates.

00:59:04.979 --> 00:59:06.486
Even worse.

00:59:06.486 --> 00:59:07.602
There's no romance in that.

00:59:07.602 --> 00:59:09.126
What do you think men are,

00:59:09.126 --> 00:59:10.470
persimmons hanging from a tree?

00:59:10.470 --> 00:59:11.731
Just waiting to fall into your lap?

00:59:11.731 --> 00:59:13.936
Blind dates are

00:59:13.936 --> 00:59:16.629
the most natural way to meet someone.

00:59:17.563 --> 00:59:20.449
How is that natural?

00:59:21.223 --> 00:59:22.242
Think about our age,

00:59:22.242 --> 00:59:25.430
our time, our energy levels.

00:59:25.430 --> 00:59:27.281
Do you have time after work

00:59:27.281 --> 00:59:29.500
to join a book club and debate philosophy?

00:59:29.500 --> 00:59:31.357
Do you have the stamina

00:59:31.357 --> 00:59:33.447
to stay up all night partying at a hostel?

00:59:33.447 --> 00:59:34.851
- No.
- Exactly.

00:59:34.851 --> 00:59:37.711
Blind dates are the most realistic option.

00:59:39.602 --> 00:59:41.933
The people who go on blind dates

00:59:41.933 --> 00:59:44.638
are the ones ready for love.

00:59:44.638 --> 00:59:46.349
All you have to do is

00:59:46.349 --> 00:59:49.008
see if you and that person click.

00:59:49.008 --> 00:59:50.825
How simple is that?

00:59:50.825 --> 00:59:54.251
Someone who's decided on love.

00:59:57.611 --> 00:59:58.672
I'll do it.

00:59:58.672 --> 01:00:00.915
Good. Do it.

01:00:00.915 --> 01:00:02.492
I'm going on a blind date!

01:00:02.492 --> 01:00:04.435
Okay, let's go.

01:00:04.435 --> 01:00:06.414
All right.

01:00:11.697 --> 01:00:13.383
Good morning.

01:00:13.383 --> 01:00:15.627
- Good morning, sir.
- There's a leak at the kitchen sink...

01:00:15.627 --> 01:00:16.677
Yes, sir.

01:00:16.677 --> 01:00:18.903
Good morning.

01:00:18.903 --> 01:00:20.107
Hello, General Manager.

01:00:20.107 --> 01:00:22.273
I'll do it.

01:00:22.273 --> 01:00:24.433
Do what?

01:00:25.560 --> 01:00:29.024
The blind date you mentioned before.

01:00:29.024 --> 01:00:31.257
Is it still an option?

01:00:38.984 --> 01:00:42.243
That's how I ended up here.

01:01:02.456 --> 01:01:04.353
It was a surprise setup,

01:01:04.353 --> 01:01:05.793
so I crammed a little.

01:01:05.793 --> 01:01:08.513
You can start the conversation naturally.

01:01:08.513 --> 01:01:11.078
Talking about the matchmaker
is also a good topic.

01:01:11.078 --> 01:01:12.143
Remember this.

01:01:12.143 --> 01:01:15.790
Talking about someone you both know

01:01:15.790 --> 01:01:18.456
builds closeness.

01:01:22.078 --> 01:01:24.568
I heard you met my General Manager

01:01:24.568 --> 01:01:27.698
through volunteering at an animal shelter.

01:01:27.698 --> 01:01:31.005
You walk the dogs like ten kilometers?

01:01:32.232 --> 01:01:33.816
I love dogs,

01:01:33.816 --> 01:01:36.169
but I'm allergic, so I can't have one.

01:01:36.169 --> 01:01:39.375
It's good exercise for me, too.

01:01:40.316 --> 01:01:43.749
Do you have any pictures?

01:01:45.702 --> 01:01:48.498
That's adorable.

01:01:48.498 --> 01:01:50.296
Such a baby.

01:01:50.296 --> 01:01:53.158
I really love dogs too.

01:01:53.158 --> 01:01:54.959
If you like dogs,

01:01:54.959 --> 01:01:58.232
maybe we could volunteer together sometime.

01:01:58.232 --> 01:02:00.365
"Sometime?"

01:02:02.526 --> 01:02:06.599
Did he just casually plan a next time with me?

01:02:20.540 --> 01:02:23.875
Do you live with your parents?

01:02:23.875 --> 01:02:26.263
No. I've been living

01:02:26.263 --> 01:02:29.063
on my own for a while.

01:02:29.679 --> 01:02:32.023
I've only ever lived with my mom,

01:02:32.023 --> 01:02:33.367
so I'm curious.

01:02:33.367 --> 01:02:35.185
What's it like?

01:02:35.185 --> 01:02:35.977
It's comfortable.

01:02:35.977 --> 01:02:38.503
You clean and do laundry when you want.

01:02:38.503 --> 01:02:40.652
Sleep whenever.

01:02:41.561 --> 01:02:43.685
But even if it's less convenient,

01:02:43.685 --> 01:02:45.798
sometimes it's better having someone with you.

01:02:45.798 --> 01:02:48.775
Food tastes better when you eat together.

01:02:48.775 --> 01:02:50.928
When I'm alone,

01:02:50.928 --> 01:02:52.289
I usually just grab something quick.

01:02:52.289 --> 01:02:53.818
Really?

01:02:53.818 --> 01:02:54.829
No, you can't do that.

01:02:54.829 --> 01:02:58.083
If you live alone,
you have to take better care of yourself.

01:02:58.083 --> 01:03:00.942
Pay attention to how you're feeling.

01:03:00.942 --> 01:03:03.974
Eat properly.

01:03:05.049 --> 01:03:07.902
Yeah, I will.

01:03:07.902 --> 01:03:09.312
But...

01:03:09.312 --> 01:03:10.845
Once you start dating,

01:03:10.845 --> 01:03:13.139
it can distract you from work.

01:03:13.139 --> 01:03:16.259
Is that okay?

01:03:16.259 --> 01:03:19.185
Love that distracts you from work?

01:03:19.989 --> 01:03:22.839
I'd love to try that.

01:03:22.839 --> 01:03:26.288
That just means they matter that much.

01:03:28.676 --> 01:03:29.772
Then...

01:03:29.772 --> 01:03:33.070
I have one more question.

01:03:33.070 --> 01:03:34.661
If you have a question,

01:03:34.661 --> 01:03:36.881
that means you're curious about me, right?

01:03:36.881 --> 01:03:39.258
This is going so smoothly.

01:03:39.258 --> 01:03:42.044
Yes, go ahead.

01:03:42.865 --> 01:03:44.543
Blood type O. MBTI is ENFP.

01:03:44.543 --> 01:03:46.775
Zodiac Sign is Cancer. Homebody. Early riser.

01:03:46.775 --> 01:03:47.941
Favorite season is winter...

01:03:47.941 --> 01:03:49.404
Ms. Ui Yeong.

01:03:49.404 --> 01:03:50.694
Are you

01:03:50.694 --> 01:03:53.318
open to dating

01:03:53.318 --> 01:03:55.721
with marriage in mind?

01:03:57.878 --> 01:03:59.478
Did you just say

01:03:59.478 --> 01:04:02.018
marriage?

01:04:02.018 --> 01:04:03.365
Yes.

01:04:03.365 --> 01:04:05.451
I...

01:04:05.451 --> 01:04:07.938
I want to get married.

01:04:09.742 --> 01:04:12.222
Smoothly? Geez.

01:04:13.089 --> 01:04:15.382
Blind dates are...

01:04:16.656 --> 01:04:19.242
the real battlefield.

01:04:41.728 --> 01:04:44.443
[I was actually his first love.]

01:04:48.526 --> 01:04:51.403
[You are still pretty.]

01:04:51.403 --> 01:04:54.607
[Here's looking at you, kid.]

01:05:02.290 --> 01:05:04.679
[Love that distracts you from work.]

01:05:09.017 --> 01:05:11.597
What if I found out by accident...

01:05:12.444 --> 01:05:14.427
A white dolphin?

01:05:14.427 --> 01:05:17.134
That his car was insanely expensive?

01:05:17.134 --> 01:05:19.154
He hasn't texted you for a second date yet?

01:05:19.154 --> 01:05:21.994
Even if he meets again later,
he should ask sooner.

01:05:21.994 --> 01:05:24.184
My phone.

01:05:24.184 --> 01:05:25.388
He's really not texting.

01:05:25.388 --> 01:05:29.583
Want me to set you up with a really solid guy?

01:05:30.462 --> 01:05:32.945
Your ex? Or your ex's ex?

01:05:32.945 --> 01:05:35.205
Are you going to keep crawling like that?

01:05:35.205 --> 01:05:36.229
Ms. Ui Yeong?

01:05:36.229 --> 01:05:38.015
I start to imagine it.

01:05:38.015 --> 01:05:39.415
What if...

01:05:39.415 --> 01:05:42.432
I just placed myself in this person's hands?

01:05:42.432 --> 01:05:45.932
Maybe it would be better than I expect.